# infra-cloudflare Cursor Rules

This repository is a multi-stack Terraform repo for Cloudflare infrastructure.

## Core model

- `stacks/<stack>/` are independent Terraform root modules
- `modules/` contains shared Terraform modules
- each stack has its own backend and state
- do not treat the repository as a single Terraform root
- use the `Makefile` as the default interface for Terraform operations

## Working style

- prefer minimal, targeted changes
- identify whether the issue is stack-local or module-wide before editing
- if editing a shared module, inspect every affected stack
- if the issue is CI-only, suspect environment/config drift before redesigning Terraform

## Repository conventions

- GitHub Actions rules are defined separately in `.cursor/rules/github-workflows.mdc`
- Terraform rules are defined separately in `.cursor/rules/terraform.mdc`
- preserve existing naming and workflow conventions unless explicitly asked to change them

## Safety baseline

- do not leak secrets in logs or code
- do not add debug dumps of environment variables
- do not break stack boundaries
- if local works but CI fails, inspect GitHub Environment and Terraform Cloud auth before assuming the Terraform code is wrong
